               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440506-name-711" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440506-name-711" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440506-name-711" type="surname" value="WHITE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440506-name-711" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES WHITE</persName>
                  </hi>. I live with my parents. I had a jacket in a box on the 27th of April, and some sixpences and coppers in my working trowsers' pocket, which I left on the chair when I went to bed—I awoke about half-past six o'clock next morning, and missed my jacket and money—this is my jacket—I know the prisoner well.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What are you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I work at ballast work—I asked the prisoner what made him rob a poor mate—he said he would not have robbed me had it not been for Peter Cavanagh—Cavanagh has made his escape—I do not know whether the prisoner had been drinking over<lb></lb>night—I had seen him at Brown's public-house, where I went to ask him about one of the lodgers.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440506-name-712" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440506-name-712" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440506-name-712" type="surname" value="RILEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440506-name-712" type="given" value="MILES"></interp>MILES RILEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I lodge in the same house with White. I lost a waistcoat that night, which contained a knife, a groat, and two pence—this is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> You did not see the prisoner in the house? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—I could not swear to him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440506-name-713" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440506-name-713" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440506-name-713" type="surname" value="GOFF"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440506-name-713" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES GOFF</persName>
                  </hi>. I live with Mr. Sowerby, a pawnbroker. This jacket and sleeve-waistcoat were pawned by the prisoner about eight o'clock in the morning on the 29th of April.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Had you seen him before? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; but I know his features, and am sure of him.</p>
               <p>
